abstracts.cdata!:
The outcome of the Fifth Highway Project
            for the Ivory Coast was successful. The project achieved
            most of its objectives, institutional development has been
            fairly successful, sustainability is likely, and the
            performance of the Bank was satisfactory while the
            Borrower's was marginally satisfactory.

abstracts.cdata!:
The project consists of: pavement
            strengthening of about 200 km of roads; realignment of a 27
            km section of the Azaguie-Adzope road and construction of
            the Anyama-Agboville road (about 45km); purchase of traffic
            counting, weight control and pavement survey equipment;
            technical assistance to establish a Planning and Research
            Unit, to improve training, and to reorganize the Public
            Works Laboratory; and pre-investment studies.
